    <body>
      <head>Hugo Becker</head>
      <div>

        <p>German virtuoso cellist.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p>A virtuoso of international repute, Becker made his solo debut with the Mannheim National
          Theater Orchestra at age sixteen. The dedicatee of solo works by <ref cRef="entity-000695"
            >Max Reger</ref>, <ref cRef="entity-000150">Eugen d’Albert</ref>, and <ref
            cRef="entity-000169">Ernst Dohnányi</ref>, Becker achieved renown for chamber work with
            <ref cRef="entity-000233">Carl Flesch</ref> and Carl Friedberg. He taught at the <ref
            cRef="entity-002625">Hochsches Conservatory</ref> and the Royal Swedish Academy before
          being appointed to the faculty of the <ref cRef="entity-002800">Berlin Hochschule für
            Musik</ref> in 1909.</p>
      </div>

    </body>

